cs.CE, cs.DL, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PL

The paper discusses computing tools and techniques for researchers, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the emphasis on "good enough" practices and the focus on researchers who are new to computing suggest that the paper is more likely to be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which deals with the development and use of computational methods in scientific research. Additionally, the mention of Data Carpentry workshops suggests a focus on data analysis and management, which could place the paper in sub-categories such as cs.DL (Digital Libraries) or cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses software development practices, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
